<body id="pc_controller_board__battery___removal">

    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">PC Controller Board, Battery - Removal</h1>

    
    <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">Removal of the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Battery, lithium, for PC Controller Board</span></em>.</p>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Stop antenna rotation (if active) with the <em class="ph i">Radar Service
                    Application</em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Switch “Mains Off” with the <em class="ph i">Radar Service Application</em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Turn off power to the transceiver with the power switch on the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Power Supply Unit (PSU)</span></em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Take out the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">PC Controller Board</span></em> (see <a class="xref" href="#pc_controller_board__battery___removal__PC_Board">Figure 1</a>)
                    and
                    place it on an ESD approved workstation.</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="pc_controller_board__battery___removal__PC_Board"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 1. </span>PC Board</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/030-10-2204-00A-fig1.png" />
                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Locate the green, cylindrical battery, which is fastened to the PCB with a
                    cable strap (see <a class="xref" href="#pc_controller_board__battery___removal__Battery">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="pc_controller_board__battery___removal__Battery"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 2. </span>Battery</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/030-10-2204-00A-fig2.png" />
                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Cut the strap, which fixes the battery to the PCB.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Disconnect the red/black wire from the connector.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Remove the battery.</span>
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

</body>
